<section xml:id="getting-swift">
  <title>Getting Swift</title>
  <para>
    Swift's source code is hosted on github and managed with git. The
    current trunk can be checked out like this:
  </para>
  <blockquote>
    <para>
      <literal>git clone https://github.com/openstack/swift.git</literal>
    </para>
  </blockquote>
  <para>
    A source tarball for the latest release of Swift is available on the
    <link xlink:href="https://launchpad.net/swift">launchpad project
    page</link>.
  </para>
  <para>
    Prebuilt packages for Ubuntu are available starting with Natty, or
    from PPAs for earlier releases.
  </para>
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <link xlink:href="https://launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/swift">Swift
        Ubuntu Packages</link>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <link xlink:href="https://launchpad.net/~swift-core/+archive/release">Swift
        PPA Archive</link>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
</section>
